
[1]calvary

   CALVARY, n.

   1. A place of skulls; particularly, the place where Christ was
   crucified, on a small hill west of Jerusalem. In catholic countries, a
   kind of chapel raised on a hillock near a city, as a place of devotion,
   in memory of the place where our Savior suffered.

   2. In heraldry, a cross so called, set upon steps, resembling the cross
   on which our Savior was crucified.
